        <body>
            <pb facs="MSVIIIp44"/>
            <div type="poem">
                <lg type="stanza" n="1" rhyme="abab" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|+/-+|-+|-+|"> <!--Meter is incredibly irregular. Not sure how to code-->
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>I weary for the torrent leaping <!-- Unsure of what the following numbers signify. They are neither line numbers or stanza numbers. They are written in possibly by John James and are located along side each stanza except the forth stanza. They are also written in pencil instead of ink. --><space quantity="5" unit="chars"/><add rend="number-right" hand="#JJR">1</add></l>
                    <l>from off the <del rend="strikethrough">mountain</del> <add place="below"><space quantity="14" unit="chars"/>scars rough</add> crest</l>
                    <l>My muse is on the mountain sleeping</l>
                    <l>My harp is sunk to rest</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" n="2" rhyme="cdcd">
                    <l>I weary for the fountain foaming</l>
                    <l>for shady holme &#x0026; hill <space quantity="12" unit="chars"/><add hand="#JJR">2</add></l>
                    <l>My mind is on the mountain roaming</l>
                    <l>My lyres voice is still.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" n="3" rhyme="efef">
                    <l>I weary for the woodland brook</l>
                    <l>that wanders through the vale <space quantity="5" unit="chars"/><add hand="#JJR">3</add></l>
                    <l><del rend="strikethrough">That</del> I weary for the heights that look</l>
                    <l>a down upon the dale</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" n="4" rhyme="ghgh">        
                    <l>The crags are lone on <placeName corresp="#CONISTONE">Conistone</placeName></l>
                    <l>&#x0026; <del rend="strikethrough"><geogName corresp="#GLARAMARA">Glaramaras</geogName></del> <add place="above"><space quantity="7" unit="chars"/><geogName corresp="#LOWESWATER">Loweswaters</geogName></add> dell</l>
                    <l>And dreary on the mighty one <space quantity="5" unit="chars"/><add hand="#JJR">4</add></l>
                    <l>The cloud enwreathed <geogName corresp="#SCAFELL">Scawfell</geogName></l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" n="5" rhyme="ijij">  
                    <l>Oh what although the crags be stern</l>
                    <l>Their craggy peaks that sever <space quantity="6" unit="chars"/><add hand="#JJR">5</add></l>
                    <l>Fresh flies the breeze on mountain fern</l>
                    <l>And free on mountain heather</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" n="6" rhyme="klkl">
                    <l>There is at thrill of strange delight</l>
                    <l>That passeth quivering oer me <space quantity="5" unit="chars"/><add hand="#JJR">6</add></l>
                    <l>When blue hills fade upon the sight</l>
                    <l>Like summer clouds before</l>
                </lg>
                <pb facs="MSVIIIp45"/>
                <lg type="stanza" n="7" rhyme="mnmn">
                    <l>Tis transient, as the <del rend="strikethrough">winters</del> <add place="above"><space quantity="21" unit="chars"/>snowy</add> drift</l>
                    <l>That passeth away</l>
                    <l>Its <!-- Unsure if the preceding word is 'Its' or 'Tis'.--> like the blush of morn that swift</l>
                    <l>Doth melt into the day</l>
					<!-- This stanza is not number like the rest. Does this mean it should be excluded from the final version? -->
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" n="8" rhyme="opop">
                    <l>I long to tread the mountain head</l>
                    <l>Above the valley swelling <space quantity="10" unit="chars"/><add hand="#JJR">6</add></l><!-- Second author gives this stanza the same number as the stanza before the exclusion.-->
                    <l>I long to feel the breeze fled <add hand="#JJR">sped</add> <!-- sped is added in by JJR, or the same hand the numbers beside stanzas are written. It seems as though he wants to replace fled with sped, but he did not override the original text with a deletion.--></l>
                    <l>From grey &#x0026; gaunt <geogName corresp="#HELVELLYN">Helvellyn</geogName>.</l>
                </lg>
                
                <lg type="stanza" n="9" rhyme="qrqr">
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJJR" script="cursive" medium="pencil"/>I love the eddying circling sweep</l>
                    <l>The mantling and the foam <space quantity="8" unit="chars"/><add hand="#JJR">7</add></l>
                    <l>Of murmuring waters dark and deep</l>
                    <l>Amid the valleys lone</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza" n="10" rhyme="qsqs">
                    <l>It is a terror, yet tis sweet <space quantity="10" unit="chars"/><add hand="#JJR">8</add></l>
                    <l>Upon some broken brow</l>
                    <l>To look upon the distant sweep</l>
                    <l>Of <del rend="strikethrough">lake or</del> ocean spread below</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
